-reef setting in the southern Arabian Gulf (Dubai, UAE): fauna and community structure in response to recurring mass mortality (1999) Coral Reefs, 18, pp. 63-73; Riegl, B.M., Purkis, S.J., Model of coral population response to accelerated bleaching and mass mortality in a changing climate (2009) Ecological Modelling, 220, pp. 192-208; Rowan, R., Coral bleaching: thermal adaptation in reef coral symbionts (2004) Nature, 430, p. 742; Sadrinasab, M., Kämpf, J., Three-dimensional flushing times of the Persian Gulf (2004) Geophysical Research Letters, 31, pp. L24301; Sheppard, C., Al-Husiani, M., Al-Jamali, F., Al-Yamani, F., Baldwin, R., Bishop, J., Benzoni, F., Zainal, K., The Gulf: a young sea in decline (2010) Marine Pollution Bulletin, 60, pp. 13-38; Sheppard, C.R.C., Predicted recurrences of mass coral mortality in the Indian Ocean (2003) Nature, 425, pp. 294-297; Shinn, E.A., Submarine lithification of Holocene carbonate sediments in the Persian Gulf (1969) Sedimentology, 12, pp. 109-144; Sillen, L.G., The ocean as a chemical system (1967) Science, 156, pp. 1189-1197; Uchupi, E., Swift, S.A., Ross, D.A., Gas venting and late quaternary sedimentation in the Persian (Arabian) Gulf (1996) Marine Geology, 129, pp. 237-269; Venn, A.A., Tambutté, E., Lotto, S., Zoccola, D., Allemand, D., Tambutté, S., Imaging intracellular pH in a reef coral and symbiotic anemone (2009) Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 106, pp. 16574-16579; Veron, J.E.N., Hoegh-Guldberg, O., Lenton, T.M., Lough, J.M., Obura, D.O., Pearce-Kelly, P., Sheppard, C.R.C., Rogers, A.D., The coral reef crisis: the critical importance of <350ppm CO2 (2009) Marine Pollution Bulletin, 58, pp. 1428-1436; Wagner, C.W., van der Togt, C., Holocene sediment types and their distribution in the southern Persian Gulf (1973) The Persian Gulf; Holocene Carbonate Sedimentation and Diagenesis in A Shallow Epicontinental Sea, pp. 123-155. , Springer-Verlag, Berlin, New York, B.H. Purser (Ed.)","Purkis, S.J.; Na